#comment in python is a line of code that is not executed by the interpreter. It is used to explain the code and make it more readable. In python we can use single line comment and multi line comment. Single line comment is created using # symbol and multi line comment is created using triple quotes (''' ''') or (""" """). Comments are ignored by the interpreter and are not executed as part of the program. They are used to provide explanations, document the code, and make it easier for other programmers to understand the code.